option.name: LAST_COMMIT_MESSAGE
option.value: Fixed bug in handling of dividerPosition nodes for splitPanes. Added region node to ContainerFactory. tableColumn can now take a String value object for the column name.

MESSAGE.value: IDEA project files for new project layout.
Fixed typo in spelling of progressIndicator control.
Fixed a problem with setting items on the choiceBox and created a simple new demo to test it.

No longer return chart builders from XYChartFactory - it was causing exceptions when charts were placed into GridPanes when the constraint factory was trying to cast the builders to Nodes. As a rule, we should always return Nodes rather than Builders from the newInstance methods from now on (excepting those factories that create non-scene graph objects, of course). That will make it easier for the rest of GroovyFX if they can always assume they are working with actual Nodes.
Added rowConstraints and columnConstraints for GridPane. Right now they are child nodes, but this can be changed easily.

Gave GridPaneDemo a face lift, and updated WebViewDemo (since it wasn't working) to include the new layout constraints as well. Rewrote the constraints processing in NodeFactory to eliminate some duplication.
Added the ability to specify gradient stops like [red, black]. Similar to the new CSS syntax, this will distribute the stops evenly between 0 and 1.0.
Using new stops syntax where it makes sense.
New syntax for stops that handles strings: "#ff00ff" in the stop list. New ColorfulCirclesDemo.

Now support key frame syntax of:
change obj.someProperty() to val tween linear
The old version that includes the closure is still supported as well. Added a new VanishingCircles demo for the J1 talk on alternative languages and updated other existing animation demos to use the new syntax.
Fixed a bug with populating the circles list.
Added ability to assume a source object in a contextual binding.
Moved license to the top of the file.
Added ability for scenes to take lists of URIs as well as URI strings. Minor changes to some demos for JavaOne presentations.
Changed handling of items property for ChoiceBox so that it can be bound.
Fixed bug in handling of dividerPosition nodes for splitPanes. Added region node to ContainerFactory. tableColumn can now take a String value object for the column name.
